These run script templates are dedicated to code for running the SCHF calculation associated with
the mean-field description of the NN Coulomb repulsion, resulting in a CDW order.

General conventions:
pval and qval are the {p, q} appearing in the Schlafli symbol for hyperbolic lattices
nval is the number of generations (unlike paper in code we start counting from 1 not 0)
alpha_NH is the alpha appearing in the NH construction, controlling the strength of the NH
small_disorder_strength is the small disorder added to stabilize the NH eigensolver
coulomb_v_value is the V parameter which controls the strength of the NN Coulomb repulsion
t is the hopping amplitude (in the corresponding work always set to 1)
beta is the parameter that controls the strength of the magnetic field (beta * # of plaquettes = total magnetic flux)

system_data is the system averaged CDW order parameter results for each V calculated for
center_data is the center plaquette site averaged CDW order parameter results for each V calculated for
raw_data is the delta values on each site for each V value calculated for
the format of raw_data is a 2D array with the first column being the V value associated with each row

